  "explanation": "While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty and employer trust, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration in this sentencing. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has demonstrated a willingness to make amends by voluntarily making partial restitution prior to sentencing. The amount taken, $25,000, warrants a penalty, but a lengthy prison term is not strictly necessary given the lack of prior offenses and the non-violent nature of the crime. Therefore, a brief period of incarceration is appropriate to serve as both a punishment and a deterrent, which will be followed by a period of supervised probation and a strict mandate to complete full restitution of the remaining embezzled funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
